There is likewi&s;e another hi&s;tory of an <HI>hypochondriacal</HI>
man, who upon u&s;ing the warm <HI>Bath,</HI> found al&s;o &s;uch a
&s;cum, which grew every day more and more <HI>corro&s;ive,</HI>
and &s;melled &s;o foetid, that they were obliged to infu&s;e
fre&s;h herbs to correct the noi&s;ome &s;tench, as well as the
<HI>Acrimony</HI> of the water, which even affected the hand
