to the &s;urface of the body, where it finds a free exit?
I believe both the one and the other may be &s;ucce&s;sfully
u&s;ed on this occa&s;ion, under proper cautions and re&s;tric|tions.
Warm Bathing, in the beginning, will relax the
fibres, widen the &s;trainer of the &s;kin, quicken the circula|tion,
and promote the &s;ecretions of urine and &s;weat, by
which the <HI>Virus</HI> may be di&s;charged before it has had time
