in the &s;ame manner as when cupping-gla&s;&s;es are ap|plied,
in order to make a <HI>Revul&s;ion,</HI> by removing the pre&s;|&s;ure
of the <HI>Atmo&s;phere.</HI></P>
<P>Although &s;uch benefits are obtained from the <HI>Vapour</HI>
of &s;imple hot Water; we know how to reinforce its vir|tues,
&s;o as to render it much more efficacious; and readi|ly
<PB N="27" REF="29">
allow, that, in this form, the hot mineral Springs are
