of the skin, but al&s;o by the <HI>Saliva</HI> and <HI>Re&s;piration.</HI> The
air contiguous to the bathing places at <HI>Bath,</HI> in <HI>Somer&s;et|&s;hire,</HI>
is &s;urcharged with <HI>Sulphur</HI> to &s;uch a degree, as to
