except in tho&s;e ca&s;es, where their <HI>&s;typtic</HI> or <HI>a&s;tringent</HI> qua|lity
may be of &s;ervice, namely in &s;ome particular kinds of
ulcers, and <HI>oedematous</HI> &s;wellings; and that, in general, the
mo&s;t effectual way of applying them externally is in form
of <HI>Vapour,</HI> whether conveyed to one particular part, or
