during a whole age; the public hath not, as yet,
been favoured with the hi&s;tory of one cure performed un|der
the au&s;pices of that charity. Dr. <HI>Summers,</HI> phy&s;ician
in that place, hath indeed, of late, publi&s;hed an accurate
account of the &s;ucce&s;s of Warm B$thing in paralytic di&s;|orders,
and, from the books of the ho&s;pital, favoured us
with a li&s;t of all the paralytic patients who have received
