to that gentleman: but, as he him&s;elf ju&s;tly ob&s;erves,
the &s;ame public <HI>hath a right to be informed how far their
$word$ intentions have been an&s;wered; and what good their
<PB N="31" REF="33">
Benevolence has produced:</HI> and this information can only
be conveyed in a &s;$ccinct detail of all the ca&s;es in which
the Warm Bath has proved &s;erviceable or deterimental.
Many people were induced to contribute largely, by the&s;e
