of oppo&s;ition was rai&s;ed again&s;t the author, who&s;e reputa|tion
<PB N="33" REF="35">
with the public could not fail to excite the malevo|lence
of &s;ome narrow-minded people of the profe&s;&s;ion,
who had acquired plentiful fortunes by their practice,
